still using SC as a placeholder for good music I find. Glad to see a lot of people enjoying the same stuff as me, so I guess ill update my profile from time to time from now on

Been on this site for a number of years now, its funny when I go back I was never interested in music. Until after highschool, I really didn't listen to music at all, that is until I discovered the mainstream, and that there was stuff out there that wasnt a part of it. Glorious is the internet in a lot of ways. Well its become a bit of a passion of mine now, and I use places like SC to obsessively hoard all the greatest music big and small from unknown corners of the internet, like a hoarder who cant get rid of anything like all. So ive got a bit of a collection now, most of it stored elsewhere (frustrated with things constantly disappearing because of SC payment model) and im slowly transitioning the best of the best over to here.

If your looking to hear something a bit different, theres a good chance you'll hear something you've never heard before in my collection if you dig around a bit. (many songs are slotted into several categories if they all fit or its a great song I want to make sure I hear again).

Starting to produce, but im barely a beginner. Hopefully I can put some of my own original things together soon. 

(the name is because it wouldnt let me use any version of my real name)

P.S. anyone know how to edit the position of playlists? trying to organize and categorize some stuff better. Kinda wondering if you can customize profiles too

The Brothers started hosting parties in 2002. With some good friends, Djs and musicians they ran the popular House nights for 8 years in Switzerland. In 2011, The Brothers label was born and got busy producing its own music.

"The Brothers label" seeks collaboration with different producers and labels worldwide who also love smoking groove that toys with heavy beats and an injection of old school house style filtered key stabs for the late night floors.

The debut single ‘Breathless’ was released in Spring 2011 with vocalist Lisa Millet and remixes from Louis Benedetti. Ever since, The Brothers has released premier Soulful House cuts on its own label of the same name, including artists such as The Rumors, Amadar, Audiowhores, Terry Hunter, Franky Fresh, The Brothers feat. Jim C, Victor Simonelli, Roberto de Carlo, Ralf Gum, Aaron Ross, Mirco Esposito and Mike La Funk, to name a few.

Also in 2011, "The Brothers label" unleashed a brand new project with the complete overhaul of top German house production duo Knee Deep's fantastic back catalog – a transformation into a brand new selection of singles which will be released as a full compilation. Each song will be remixed by a well known artist in the house music scene, including the likes of Terry Hunter, Bobby D’Ambrosio, Louis Benedetti, Aaron Ross and The Brothers themselves.

Another milestone has been added in 2013, with the label "The Brothers Track" - the channel for Deep and Tech House Releases.

What a breakthrough year 2019 was for the industrious and incessantly hard-working London based DJ & producer Sammy Porter.

His debut release on MistaJam’s Speakerbox Records “What We Started (A Bit Patchy)” has now amassed almost 14 million streams worldwide with over 2500 UK radio spins. Porter then continued to smash the UK dance floors and radio waves with his follow up smash “Talking Like Friends”, enlisting the vocal talents of Liv Dawson (Disclosure, Meeting Music), setting the bar even higher.

Now he is set to unleash a further assault on club and radio airwaves worldwide with his new cut “Let Your Love” released 6th December 2019 again on the Speakerbox imprint, under the Insanity Records & Sony Music UK umbrella.

As label boss and main resident for the hugely popular UK house brand LoveJuice, Porter has played some of the biggest dance events of the year @ We Are FSTVL, Electric Brixton, E1 London, with many more. high capacity shows booked for 2020. Sammy Porter has cemented himself as a key tastemaker from the UK House scene with regular gigs for Ministry of Sound, Audiowhore and House Of Silk to name a few.

As one of the leading DJs on the circuit, a relentless touring scheduled has allowed Porter to continue to smash dance floors & festivals across the globe. From London to Ibiza, Malta to Marbella and Dubai, regular shows at countless party destinations means Sammy is hotly in demand like never before.

Further cementing his status as an ambassador of the scene, Sammy continues to develop his skills as a radio DJ & presenter with regular slots on Rinse FM as well as certifying himself as a hot remix artist after being asked to remix the likes of Clean Bandit, James Hype, M-22 & Jack Wins. Meanwhile having more club driven remixes for Glasgow Underground, Dirty Vegas, The Original and Degrees In Motion he is certifying his ear for both the more commercial and underground sound spaces.

Darkside is an electronic ambient music duo featuring Nicolas Jaar and Dave Harrington. Together, they produce quite a minimal, experimental sound. Harrington plays guitars and other instruments while Jaar sings ambient vocals and produces the electronic beats. Jaar and Harrington met while attending Brown University. Producer Jaar was looking for a third musician to join himself and Will Epstein on a tour to promote his debut solo album, "Space is Only Noise". While touring in Berlin, Jaar and Harrington began working on new music together which eventually became Darkside’s first EP. In 2011, independent label Clown & Sunset released "Darkside EP" which earned an 8.0 from music critic website Pitchfork. They made their live debut later that year to a sold out crowd at Music Hall of Williamsburg in New York, which then earned them a spot at the 2012 South by Southwest Music Festival.  In 2013, Darkside released a remix of Daft Punk's newest album, which they called "Random Access Memories Memories", under the name Daftside. The remix earned multiple positive reviews and earned the attention of the independent label Matador Records. In October of that year, Darkside released its debut album ‘Psychic’. The album marked the band's transition from strictly experimental ambient, to more down tempo electro pop. It climbed to #163 on the US Billboard 200, reaching number six on US Dance albums. The album also saw considerable success in the UK indie scene, peaking at #21. After completing a world tour in 2014, Jaar and Harrington announced a hiatus which will last for an unspecified length of time.
